# Dependencies
node_modules/

# Build output
dist/
dist-zip/

# Vite cache
.vite/
vite.config.ts.timestamp-*

# TypeScript
*.tsbuildinfo

# Environment & secrets
.env
.env.local
.env.*.local
.env.development
.env.production
*.pem
*.key
*.cert
secrets.*
config.local.*

# OS
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
desktop.ini

# Editor
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp
*.swo
*~

# Logs
*.log
npm-debug.log*
yarn-debug.log*
pnpm-debug.log*

# Package manager locks (keep only one — this project uses npm)
yarn.lock
pnpm-lock.yaml

# Chrome extension packaging artifacts
*.crx
*.pem
*.zip

# Test coverage
coverage/
.nyc_output/

# Temp / scratch
*.tmp
*.temp
.cache/
```

Key points:
- `node_modules/` and `dist/` never committed — biggest ones
- `.env*` files block any API keys or secrets you might add later
- `*.pem` blocks the Chrome extension signing key (if you ever package with `chrome.exe --pack-extension` it generates a `.pem` — that key must **never** go to git)
- `*.crx` blocks packaged extension binaries
- Only `package-lock.json` kept — `yarn.lock` and `pnpm-lock.yaml` excluded since project uses npm